根据BBC的报道，2009年，世界上有23%人口是[[穆斯林|穆斯林]]，其中60%的穆斯林来自亚洲。<ref name="Pew Reference #2 (from BBC site)">{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/8296200.stm|title=One in four is Muslim, study says|last=|first=|publisher=BBC News Website|accessdate=|date=2009-10-08|archive-date=2020-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308195819/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/8296200.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Pew Reference #2 (from BBC site)"/>从1990年到2010年，世界穆斯林人口平均每年增长2.2%，预计2030年穆斯林将占到全世界人口26.4%，这主要是因为穆斯林国家的出生率普遍较高。<ref>[http://www.pewforum.org/The-Future-of-the-Global-Muslim-Population.aspx "The Future of Global Muslim Population: Projections from 2010 to 2013"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.pewforum.org/The-Future-of-the-Global-Muslim-Population.aspx |date=20130723032443 }} Accessed July 2013.</ref><ref>Barrett, David A.  [http://www.bible.ca/global-religion-statistics-world-christian-encyclopedia.htm "Global Statistics for all religions: 2001 AD, Table 1:1"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bible.ca/global-religion-statistics-world-christian-encyclopedia.htm |date=20171020054455 }}, accessed May 7, 2011. Referencing “World Christian Encyclopedia”, 2001, p. 4.</ref><ref>Huntington, Samuel. [http://books.google.com/books?id=LO4xG-bH1CQC&printsec=frontcover&dq=The+Clash+of+Civilizations+and+the+Remaking+of+World+Order&hl=en&sa=X&ei=J7ziUa2rGoLfrAH-y4CADA&ved=0CC8Q6AEwAA "The Clash of Civilizations and the Remaking of World Order,"] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=LO4xG-bH1CQC&printsec=frontcover&dq=The+Clash+of+Civilizations+and+the+Remaking+of+World+Order&hl=en&sa=X&ei=J7ziUa2rGoLfrAH-y4CADA&ved=0CC8Q6AEwAA |date=20131009041253 }} Touchstone Books, 1998, p. 65-66.</ref><ref>Robinson, B. A. [http://www.religioustolerance.org/worldrel.htm] {{Wayback|url=http://www.religioustolerance.org/worldrel.htm |date=20180917191913 }}, Religious Tolerence.org, “Numbers of adherents; names of houses of worship; names of leaders; rates of growth...”, 1997 -2009, accessed May 5, 2011.</ref>

某些研究认为穆斯林的人口增长几乎全部靠“出生率”驱动，即该信仰群体拥有大量的新生者，同时老年信众的预期寿命也有所提高。而“后天皈依”的人很少，几乎没有推动伊斯兰教人口增长。<ref>Survey of 19 nations in Sub-Sahara Africa conducted in 2009, published in the Pew Forum’s April 2010 report [http://www.pewforum.org/executive-summary-islam-and-christianity-in-sub-saharan-africa.aspx "Tolerance and Tension: Islam and Christianity in Sub-Saharan Africa."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.pewforum.org/executive-summary-islam-and-christianity-in-sub-saharan-africa.aspx |date=20130725211527 }} The Pew Forum on Religion and Public Life, April 15, 2010</ref><ref>Richard Allen Greene, [http://religion.blogs.cnn.com/2011/01/27/world-muslim-population-doubling-report-projects/?hpt=C1 "World Muslim population doubling, report projects,"] {{Wayback|url=http://religion.blogs.cnn.com/2011/01/27/world-muslim-population-doubling-report-projects/?hpt=C1 |date=20130521161751 }} CNN News, January 27, 2011</ref><ref>[http://www.pewforum.org/future-of-the-global-muslim-population-related-factors-conversion.aspx "The Future of the Global Muslim Population, Related Factors: Conversion"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.pewforum.org/future-of-the-global-muslim-population-related-factors-conversion.aspx |date=20130730043256 }}, The Pew Forum on Religion and Public Life, January 27, 2011</ref>
但主流的观点认为，伊斯兰教的新皈依信徒的比例高于基督教等其他宗教，位列第一。根据2003年版的《吉尼斯世界纪录》，在1990-2000年期间，伊斯兰教的皈依人数比同时期的基督教高出近12,500,000人。<ref>Guinness World Records 2003. Guinness World Records. 2003. p. 142.</ref>

===威卡教===
[[威卡教|威卡教]]信众在20世纪90年代的美国以每年143%的速度飞速增长。2001年已经达到134,000人，是美国发展最快的宗教之一。<ref name="cuny1"/><ref name="cuny2"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.statesman.com/life/faith/our-year-long-exploration-of-religions-ends-with-2069331.html|title=Our year-long exploration of religions ends with Unitarianian Universalism and paganism|last=(Elizabeth) Wynn|first=Anne|publisher=The Statesman.com|accessdate=2 January 2012|archive-date=2012-01-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120110180758/http://www.statesman.com/life/faith/our-year-long-exploration-of-religions-ends-with-2069331.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="PRLog">{{cite news|url=http://www.prlog.org/10144283-wicca-the-fastest-growing-belief-system-in-the-world-today.html|title=PRLog (Press Release) "Wicca"- The Fastest Growing Belief System In The World Today!|publisher=PRLog|accessdate=2 January 2012|archive-date=2013-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927222814/http://www.prlog.org/10144283-wicca-the-fastest-growing-belief-system-in-the-world-today.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.azcentral.com/community/gilbert/articles/2010/10/22/20101022southeast-valley-paganism-on-rise.html|title=Rise in paganism in Southeast Valley mirrors U.S. trend|last=Puffer|first=Nancy|publisher=azcentral.com|accessdate=2 January 2012}}</ref>

===无信仰===
[[File:Bsa-religion-question.svg|thumb]]
以人数绝对值来算，无信仰者的人口是在增长当中。<ref name="aris">{{cite web |url=http://www.americanreligionsurvey-aris.org/reports/NONES_08.pdf |title=American Nones: The Profile of the No Religion Population |year=2008 |publisher=American Religious Identification Survey |accessdate=19 October 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091007012422/http://www.americanreligionsurvey-aris.org/reports/NONES_08.pdf |archivedate=2009-10-07 }}</ref>即使是这样，它在世界人口的比重仍然在下降，这主要因为世界主要的人口增长都来自宗教色彩浓厚的国家。

在美国，无信仰者人口在1990年有1430万人，2001年已经猛增到2940万人，已经占到总人口的14.1%。<ref name="cuny1"/><ref name="cuny2">[http://www.gc.cuny.edu/CUNY_GC/media/CUNY-Graduate-Center/PDF/ARIS/ARIS-PDF-version.pdf?ext=.pdf American Religious Identification Survey, Full PDF Document] {{WebCite|url=https://www.webcitation.org/6HZLgZxqv?url=http://www.gc.cuny.edu/CUNY_GC/media/CUNY-Graduate-Center/PDF/ARIS/ARIS-PDF-version.pdf?ext=.pdf |date=20130622154558 |dateformat=iso }} The Graduate Center of the City University of New York</ref>无信仰者的人数在美国增长速度超过所有其它主流宗教。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://blogs.reuters.com/faithworld/2009/09/23/no-religion-segment-of-us-population-profiled/ |title=Faith World, “No religion” segment of U.S. population profiled |accessdate=2013-07-21 |archive-date=2017-08-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170810210543/http://blogs.reuters.com/faithworld/2009/09/23/no-religion-segment-of-us-population-profiled/ |dead-url=yes }}</ref>“无信仰者”还可分为不可知论者、无神论者、和相信有神但无特定信仰者。<ref name="aris" />在2012年，美国已经有五分之一的人口无信仰，而30岁以下的年轻人无信仰者已经达到三分之一。<ref name="pew">{{cite web|url=http://www.pewforum.org/Unaffiliated/nones-on-the-rise.aspx|title='No Religion' on the Rise: One-in-Five Adults Have No Religious Affiliation|date=9 October 2012|publisher=Pew Forum on Religion & Public Life|accessdate=19 October 2012|archive-date=2018-12-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181225135016/http://www.pewforum.org/2012/10/09/nones-on-the-rise/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在澳大利亚、加拿大、墨西哥等国家，无信仰者的人口增速也非常快。在加拿大，无信仰者人口在2004年比1985年增长了60%。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.statcan.gc.ca/pub/11-008-x/2006001/9181-eng.htm |title=decline StatsCan, "Who is Religious?" by '''by Warren Clark and Grant Schellenberg |accessdate=2013-07-21 |archive-date=2017-07-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170726022940/http://www.statcan.gc.ca/pub/11-008-x/2006001/9181-eng.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>2006年的一份调查显示在澳大利亚，18.2%的人口无信仰，比以往任何年代都要多。<ref name="censusdata.abs.gov.au">{{Cite web |url=http://www.censusdata.abs.gov.au/ABSNavigation/prenav/ViewData?action=404&documentproductno=0&documenttype=Details&order=1&tabname=Details&areacode=0&issue=2006&producttype=Census%20Tables&javascript=true&textversion=false&navmapdisplayed=true&breadcrumb=POTLD&&c |title=2006 Census Table : Australia |accessdate=2013-07-21 |archive-date=2020-06-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200604125955/https://www.abs.gov.au/websitedbs/censushome.nsf/home/cowsredirect/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>在墨西哥，无神论者每年增长5.2%，而天主教的信众每年增长1.7%。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.aciprensa.com/noticia.php?n=20574Aciprensa |title=México sigue siendo católico… pero crece el número de ateos<!-- Bot generated title --> |accessdate=2013-07-21 |archive-date=2012-03-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320054919/http://www.aciprensa.com/noticia.php?n=20574Aciprensa |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.catholicnewsagency.com/new.php?n=12159 |title=Catholic News Agency |accessdate=2013-07-21 |archive-date=2009-03-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090314002357/http://www.catholicnewsagency.com/new.php?n=12159 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

